Cell.Text: [S] G|Please, stop! I'll pay! Take it!
[S] G|Please, no more. I'll pay, I'll pay. Here!
[S] G|Here... take your damn coin and get out of here!
[S] G|Well fought, ya swinging bit of skeever bait.
[S] I don't believe it. I guess you were right!
[S] Your fists speak louder than your words.
[S] You bested me, an Orc chief. Impressive.
[S] It's been so long since I tasted my own blood. Sour.
[S] Damn addicts always stealing from me.
[S] Damn it. Why'd you have to walk into Morthal?
[S] Now that's what I call a punch. You got me.
[S] Now that was a punch.
[S] Wait, I can still fight. No, no I can't.
[S] That wasn't a fair swing.
[S] Damn outsider. Why couldn't you just mind your own business?
[S] Backbiter.
[S] Damn Boot-lover.
[S] You throw a mean hook.
[S] What was that? Some kind of foreign move?
[S] You know how to throw a punch, I'll give you that.
[S] Ugh. You mangy piece of pit-bait.
[S] <<Shared>> You're tougher than you look. You got me, fair and square.
[S] <<Shared>> You're tougher than you look. You got me, fair and square.
[S] <<Shared>> I didn't mean nothing by it! Just... leave me alone! What do you want?
Now where's Esbern?

[S] G|<<Shared>> He's holed up in the Ratway Warrens. Hardly ever leaves the place - has someone bring him food and such. | Crazy old coot, from what I've heard. For that to stand out down here, he must really be off his nut.
I hope you aren't angry.
[S] G|Not at all. It's good to be put in your place once in a while. | I guess I shouldn't boast so much... it gets expensive!
I think I've earned that 100 gold.
[S] G|You're no liar. Best fight I've had in years. There you are. | You ever need another blade at your side, just ask. Wouldn't mind seeing how you handle a few trolls.
I think I've earned that 100 gold.
[S] G|You're a real fighter. I like that. | You ever need my steel by your side, you just ask.
You'll come with me, then?
[S] G|My axe is yours, outlander. Just say the word.
I've earned my coin, I think.
[S] G|That you have. Here.
You lost. Give me my money.
[S] G|Fair fight. Here you are.
Give me the hilt. Now.
[S] G|Fine. The hilt is in a chest inside my house. Here are the keys. Take that damn thing and go.
You lost. Give me my money.
[S] G|Yeah. Here.
You'll let me through now?
[S] G|Yeah, yeah. Go on in.
Now give me that skooma.
[S] G|Here. I hope you choke on it.
You leave Carlotta alone, or this gets worse.
[S] G|You win. On my honor, Carlotta won't have to worry about me ever again.
You ready to listen to reason now?
[S] G|I get your point. Tell Iddra I'm sorry for being so stubborn about the coin.
You ready to pay up now?
[S] G|You got me, fair and square. Tell Haran I'll pay.
You pay those Argonians fairly, or else.
[S] G|I yield. By the honor of Clan Shatter-Shield, the Argonians will be paid as much as any other worker.
Talk, or I send you to the gods.
[S] G|I was sent by Nepos the Nose. The old man hands out the orders. | He told me to make sure you didn't get in the way. That's all I know, I swear!
Final warning. Leave Octieve alone.
[S] G|All right. Tell the old man his debts are settled.
Leave Omluag alone. This is my final warning.
[S] G|All right. I'll lay off him. Just leave.
You know what you have to do.
[S] G|Fine! I'll take care of it, just please leave me alone!
[S] G|Get it over with, then.
[S] G|You're making a mistake!
